-- Gazprom May Buy Mitsui, Mitsubishi Stakes in Sakhalin-2, RBC Daily Reports
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2010-11-23T05:51:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-23/gazprom-may-buy-japanese-stakes-in-sakhalin-2-rbc-daily-says.html
OAO Gazprom, Russia’s gas-export
monpoly, is in talks to buy out Sakhalin-2 partners Mitsui & Co.
and Mitsubishi Corp., RBC Daily reported, citing an unidentified
official from Russia’s budget watchdog.  The two Japanese companies and Royal Dutch Shell Plc in
2007 sold control over the liquefied natural gas venture off
Russia’s Pacific coast to Gazprom.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
